ground_truth:
Read 0: pin PIOm_n is LOW. Write 0: clear output bit. Read
								0xFFFF FFFF: pin PIOm_n is HIGH. Write any value 0x0000 0001 to
								0xFFFF FFFF: set output bit. Only 0 or 0xFFFF FFFF can be read.
								Writing any value other than 0 will set the output bit. One register
								for each port pin. Supported pins depends on the specific device and
								package.

								enabled.

question: What is the description of CAPn_H field from CAP1 register from SCT0 peripheral for LPC5410x microcontroller?
ground_truth:
When UNIFY = 0, read the 16-bit counter value at which this
								register was last captured. When UNIFY = 1, read the upper 16 bits
								of the 32-bit value at which this register was last
								captured.
baseline model_output: CAPn_H If bit m is one, event m causes the CAPn_H (UNIFY = 0) register to be loaded (event 0 = bit 16, event 1 = bit 17, etc. The number of bits = number of events in this SCT.

								the INTVALn register either at the end of the time interval or
								immediately in the following cases: INTVALn register is updated in

								FFFF).

Selects the input or output signal associated with this

								every event.

What is the description of PWORD field from W24 register from GPIO peripheral for LPC5410x microcontroller?
ground_truth:
Read 0: pin PIOm_n is LOW. Write 0: clear output bit. Read
								0xFFFF FFFF: pin PIOm_n is HIGH. Write any value 0x0000 0001 to
								0xFFFF FFFF: set output bit. Only 0 or 0xFFFF FFFF can be read.
								Writing any value other than 0 will set the output bit. One register
								for each port pin. Supported pins depends on the specific device and
								package.
baseline model_output: PWORD Read 0: pin PIOm_n is LOW.
few shot model_output: PWORD Read 0: pin PIOm_n is LOW.
ft model output: PWORD Read 0: pin PIOm_n is LOW.
ft few_shot model output: PWORD Read 0: pin PIOm_n is LOW.

question: What is the description of DSTBURSTWRAP field from CFG5 register from DMA peripheral for LPC5410x microcontroller?
ground_truth:
Destination Burst Wrap. When enabled, the destination data
								address for the DMA is wrapped, meaning that the destination address
								range for each burst will be the same. As an example, this could be
								used to write several sequential registers to a peripheral for each
								DMA burst, writing the same registers again for each
								burst.
few shot model_output: DST Burst Wrap. This bit is used to enable burst wrap for the destination address.
ft few_shot model output: DST Burst Wrap. This bit is used to enable burst wrap for the destination address.

What is the description of TO field from TIMEOUT register from I2C1 peripheral for LPC5410x microcontroller?
ground_truth:
Time-out time value. Specifies the time-out interval value
								in increments of 16 I2C function clocks, as defined by the CLKDIV
								register. To change this value while I 2C is in operation, disable
								all time-outs, write a new value to TIMEOUT, then re-enable
								time-outs. 0x000 = A time-out will occur after 16 counts of the I2C
								function clock. 0x001 = A time-out will occur after 32 counts of the
								I2C function clock. ... 0xFFF = A time-out will occur after 65,536
								counts of the I2C function clock.
few shot model_output: Timeout period. This is simply a copy of the same field in the STATUS register, included here so an ISR can read all needed status information in one read.
ft few_shot model output: Timeout period. This is simply a copy of the same field in the STATUS register, included here so an ISR can read all needed status information in one read.

What is the description of RXOV field from STAT register from SPI0 peripheral for LPC5410x microcontroller?
ground_truth:
Receiver Overrun interrupt flag. This flag applies only to
								slave mode (Master = 0). This flag is set when the beginning of a
								received character is detected while the receiver buffer is still in
								use. If this occurs, the receiver buffer contents are preserved, and
								the incoming data is lost. Data received by the SPI should be
								considered undefined if RxOv is set.
baseline model_output: RXOV Receive FIFO Overflow. When 1, the receive FIFO has overflowed. This is a 0 read-only bit.
few shot model_output: RX Overrun. When 1, the receive FIFO has overflowed. This is a 0 read-only bit.
ft model output: RXOV Receive FIFO Overflow. When 1, the receive FIFO has overflowed. This is a 0 read-only bit.

question: What is the description of DIVVAL field from CLKDIV register from I2C1 peripheral for LPC5410x microcontroller?
ground_truth:
This field controls how the clock (PCLK) is used by the I2C
								functions that need an internal clock in order to operate. 0x0000 =
								PCLK is used directly by the I2C. 0x0001 = PCLK is divided by 2
								before use. 0x0002 = PCLK is divided by 3 before use. ... 0xFFFF =
								PCLK is divided by 65,536 before use.
baseline model_output: DIVVAL This field controls how the clock (PCLK) is used by the I2C functions that need an internal 0 clock in order to operate.
few shot model_output: DIVVAL Rate divider value. Specifies how the PCLK for the I2C is divided to produce the I2C clock rate in 0 master mode.
ft model output: DIVVAL This field controls how the clock (PCLK) is used by the I2C functions that need an internal 0 clock in order to operate.
ft few_shot model output: DIVVAL Rate divider value. Specifies how the PCLK for the I2C is divided to produce the I2C clock rate in 0 master mode.

ground_truth:
Timeout Continue On Write. When 0, the timeout for the
								related peripheral is reset every time data is transferred from the
								peripheral into the receive FIFO. When 1, the timeout for the
								related peripheral is not reset every time data is transferred into
								the receive FIFO. This allows the timeout to be applied to
								accumulated data, perhaps related to the FIFO
								threshold.

ONWRITE When 1, the timeout for the related peripheral is not reset every time data is transferred into the receive FIFO. This allows the timeout to be applied to accumulated data, perhaps related to the FIFO threshold.

question: What is the bit_offset of VALUE field from TIMER1 register from MRT peripheral for LPC5410x microcontroller?
What is the bit_width of TIMEOUTVALUE field from CFGSPI1 register from VFIFO peripheral for LPC5410x microcontroller?
What is the bit_offset of OUTSEL field from EV8_CTRL register from SCT0 peripheral for LPC5410x microcontroller?
What is the description of INP field from DMA_ITRIG_INMUX2 register from INPUTMUX peripheral for LPC5410x microcontroller?
ground_truth:
Trigger input number (decimal value) for DMA channel n (n =
								0 to 21). 0 = ADC0 Sequence A interrupt 1 = ADC0 Sequence B
								interrupt 2 = SCT0 DMA request 0 3 = SCT0 DMA request 1 4 = Timer 0
								Match 0 5 = Timer 0 Match 1 6 = Timer 1 Match 0 7 = Timer 2 Match 0
								8 = Timer 2 Match 1 9 = Timer 3 Match 0 10 = Timer 4 Match 0 11 =
								Timer 4 Match 1 12 = Pin interrupt 0 13 = Pin interrupt 1 14 = Pin
								interrupt 2 15 = Pin interrupt 3 16 = DMA output trigger mux 0 17 =
								DMA output trigger mux 1 18 = DMA output trigger mux 2 19 = DMA
								output trigger mux 3

ground_truth:
A 1 in bit m selects event m to set output n (or clear it
								if SETCLRn = 0x1 or 0x2) event 0 = bit 0, event 1 = bit 1, etc. The
								number of bits = number of events in this SCT.

question: What is the description of CAPn_H field from CAP11 register from SCT0 peripheral for LPC5410x microcontroller?
ground_truth:
When UNIFY = 0, read the 16-bit counter value at which this
								register was last captured. When UNIFY = 1, read the upper 16 bits
								of the 32-bit value at which this register was last
								captured.
baseline model_output: CAPn_H If bit m is one, event m causes the CAPn_H (UNIFY = 0) register to be loaded (event 0 = bit 16, event 1 = bit 17, etc. The number of bits = number of events in this SCT.
few shot model_output: CAPn_H When UNIFY = 0, read the 16-bit counter value at which this register was last captured. 0 When UNIFY = 1, read the upper 16 bits of the 32-bit value at which this register was last captured.
ft model output: CAPn_H If bit m is one, event m causes the CAPn_H (UNIFY = 0) register to be loaded (event 0 = bit 16, event 1 = bit 17, etc. The number of bits = number of events in this SCT.
ft few_shot model output: CAPn_H When UNIFY = 0, read the 16-bit counter value at which this register was last captured. 0 When UNIFY = 1, read the upper 16 bits of the 32-bit value at which this register was last captured.

ground_truth:
Read: state of the pin PIOm_n, regardless of direction,
								masking, or alternate function, except that pins configured as
								analog I/O always read as 0. One register for each port pin.
								Supported pins depends on the specific device and package. Write:
								loads the pins output bit. One register for each port pin. Supported
								pins depends on the specific device and package.

What is the description of THCMPRANGE field from DAT4 register from ADC0 peripheral for LPC5410x microcontroller?
ground_truth:
Threshold Range Comparison result. 0x0 = In Range: The last
								completed conversion was greater than or equal to the value
								programmed into the designated LOW threshold register (THRn_LOW) but
								less than or equal to the value programmed into the designated HIGH
								threshold register (THRn_HIGH). 0x1 = Below Range: The last
								completed conversion on was less than the value programmed into the
								designated LOW threshold register (THRn_LOW). 0x2 = Above Range: The
								last completed conversion was greater than the value programmed into
								the designated HIGH threshold register (THRn_HIGH). 0x3 =
								Reserved.
few shot model_output: Threshold Crossing Range. This field is hard-coded to contain the range of the threshold value established by the designated LOW threshold register (THRn_LOW) for this channel.
ft few_shot model output: Threshold Crossing Range. This field is hard-coded to contain the range of the threshold value established by the designated LOW threshold register (THRn_LOW) for this channel.

What is the description of MONIDLE field from STAT register from I2C0 peripheral for LPC5410x microcontroller?
ground_truth:
Monitor Idle flag. This flag is set when the Monitor
								function sees the I2C bus change from active to inactive. This can
								be used by software to decide when to process data accumulated by
								the Monitor function. This flag will cause an interrupt when set if
								enabled via the INTENSET register. The flag can be cleared by
								writing a 1 to this bit.
few shot model_output: Monitor Idle. This bit is set when the monitor is idle.
ft few_shot model output: Monitor Idle. This bit is set when the monitor is idle.

ground_truth:
Transmitter Disabled Status flag. When 1, this bit
								indicates that the USART transmitter is fully idle after being
								disabled via the TXDIS bit in the CFG register (TXDIS =
								1).

What is the description of INP field from DMA_ITRIG_INMUX9 register from INPUTMUX peripheral for LPC5410x microcontroller?
ground_truth:
Trigger input number (decimal value) for DMA channel n (n =
								0 to 21). 0 = ADC0 Sequence A interrupt 1 = ADC0 Sequence B
								interrupt 2 = SCT0 DMA request 0 3 = SCT0 DMA request 1 4 = Timer 0
								Match 0 5 = Timer 0 Match 1 6 = Timer 1 Match 0 7 = Timer 2 Match 0
								8 = Timer 2 Match 1 9 = Timer 3 Match 0 10 = Timer 4 Match 0 11 =
								Timer 4 Match 1 12 = Pin interrupt 0 13 = Pin interrupt 1 14 = Pin
								interrupt 2 15 = Pin interrupt 3 16 = DMA output trigger mux 0 17 =
								DMA output trigger mux 1 18 = DMA output trigger mux 2 19 = DMA
								output trigger mux 3

What is the description of SRCBURSTWRAP field from CFG5 register from DMA peripheral for LPC5410x microcontroller?
ground_truth:
Source Burst Wrap. When enabled, the source data address
								for the DMA is wrapped, meaning that the source address range for
								each burst will be the same. As an example, this could be used to
								read several sequential registers from a peripheral for each DMA
								burst, reading the same registers again for each
								burst.

question: What is the description of BRGVAL field from BRG register from USART2 peripheral for LPC5410x microcontroller?
ground_truth:
This value is used to divide the USART input clock to
								determine the baud rate, based on the input clock from the FRG. 0 =
								The FRG clock is used directly by the USART function. 1 = The FRG
								clock is divided by 2 before use by the USART function. 2 = The FRG
								clock is divided by 3 before use by the USART function. ... 0xFFFF =
								The FRG clock is divided by 65,536 before use by the USART
								function.

question: What is the description of PWORD field from W49 register from GPIO peripheral for LPC5410x microcontroller?
ground_truth:
Read 0: pin PIOm_n is LOW. Write 0: clear output bit. Read
								0xFFFF FFFF: pin PIOm_n is HIGH. Write any value 0x0000 0001 to
								0xFFFF FFFF: set output bit. Only 0 or 0xFFFF FFFF can be read.
								Writing any value other than 0 will set the output bit. One register
								for each port pin. Supported pins depends on the specific device and
								package.
few shot model_output: PWORD Read 0: pin PIOm_n is LOW.
ft few_shot model output: PWORD Read 0: pin PIOm_n is LOW.

								pins depends on the specific device and package.

question: What is the description of CAP1RE field from CCR register from CT32B1 peripheral for LPC5410x microcontroller?
ground_truth:
Rising edge of capture channel 1: a sequence of 0 then 1
								causes CR1 to be loaded with the contents of TC. 0 = disabled. 1 =
								enabled.
baseline model_output: CAP1RE Count Input Select 1 When bit 1:0 in this register are not 00, these bits select which CAP pin is sampled for clocking. Note: If Counter mode is selected for a particular CAPn input in the CTCR, the 3 bits for that input in the Capture Control Register (CCR) must be programmed as 000. However, capture and/or interrupt can be selected for the other 3 CAPn inputs in the same timer. 0x0 Channel 0. CAPn.0 for TIMERn 0x1 Channel 1. CAPn.1 for TIMERn 0x2 Channel 2. CAPn.2 for TIMERn 0x3 Channel 3. CAPn.3 for TIMERn 4 ENCC Setting this bit to 1 enables clearing of the timer and the prescaler when the 0 capture-edge event specified in bits 7:5 occurs. 7:5 SELCC Edge select. When bit 4 is 1, these bits select which capture input edge will cause 0 the timer and prescaler to be cleared. These bits have no effect when bit 4 is low. Values 0x2 to 0x3 and 0x6 to 0x7 are reserved. 0x0 Channel 0 Rising Edge. Rising edge of the signal on capture channel 0 clears the timer (if bit 4 is set). 0x1 Channel 0 Falling Edge. Falling edge of the signal on capture channel 0 clears the timer (if bit 4 is set). 0x2 Channel 1 Rising Edge. Rising edge of the signal on capture channel 1 clears the timer (if bit 4 is set). 0x3 Channel 1 Falling Edge. Falling edge of the signal on capture channel 1 clears the timer (if bit 4 is set). 0x4 Channel 2 Rising Edge. Rising edge of the signal on capture channel 2 clears the timer (if bit 4 is set). 0x5 Channel 2 Falling Edge. Falling edge of the signal on capture channel 2 clears the timer (if bit 4 is set). 31:8 - Reserved. Read value is undefined, only zero should be written.
few shot model_output: Capture 1 Enable. This bit is used to enable the capture of CAP1. When this bit is set, the CAP1 value is sampled and stored in CAP1 register. This bit is cleared by writing 1 to it. This bit is always enabled and does not need to be written.

However, capture and/or interrupt can be selected for the other 3 CAPn inputs in the same timer. 0x0 Channel 0. CAPn.0 for TIMERn 0x1 Channel 1. CAPn.1 for TIMERn 0x2 Channel 2. CAPn.2 for TIMERn 0x3 Channel 3.
